---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Privacy Policy — GenSnitch" description="Privacy policy for the GenSnitch Chrome extension.">
  <article class="content">
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="updated">Last updated: December 2025</p>

    <section>
      <h2>Overview</h2>
      <p>
        GenSnitch is designed with privacy as a core principle. We believe your browsing activity 
        is your business—not ours.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Data Collection</h2>
      <p>
        <strong>We do not collect, store, or transmit any personal data.</strong>
      </p>
      <p>
        GenSnitch operates entirely on your device. The extension analyzes image metadata locally 
        in your browser. No images are ever uploaded to external servers.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Permissions</h2>
      <p>The extension requests only the minimum permissions necessary:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>contextMenus</strong> — To create the right-click menu option.</li>
        <li><strong>activeTab</strong> — To access images on the current page when you activate the extension.</li>
        <li><strong>storage</strong> — To save analysis reports temporarily.</li>
        <li><strong>scripting</strong> — To fetch blob: URLs from page context.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>We do not request broad browsing history access or any permissions beyond what's essential.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Third-Party Services</h2>
      <p>GenSnitch does not integrate with any third-party analytics, tracking, or advertising services.</p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Changes to This Policy</h2>
      <p>
        If we update this policy, we'll revise the "Last updated" date above. Material changes 
        will be communicated through the extension's update notes.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section>
      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>
        Questions about this policy? Open an issue on 
        <a href="https://github.com/Stasieniec/gensnitch" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">GitHub</a>.
      </p>
    </section>
  </article>
</Layout>

<style>
  .content {
    max-width: 640px;
  }

  h1 {
    font-size: 2rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .updated {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: var(--text-muted);
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
  }

  section {
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
  }

  h2 {
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  p {
    color: var(--text-muted);
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  p:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }

  strong {
    color: var(--text);
    font-weight: 500;
  }

  ul {
    list-style: none;
    margin: 1rem 0;
  }

  li {
    color: var(--text-muted);
    padding-left: 1.25rem;
    position: relative;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  li::before {
    content: "•";
    color: var(--accent);
    position: absolute;
    left: 0;
  }

  a {
    color: var(--accent);
    text-decoration: underline;
    text-underline-offset: 2px;
  }

  a:hover {
    text-decoration: none;
  }
</style>

